E4Plus1.uk.description: The Hawking Excitation: When Stephen Hawking comes to lecture at the university, Howard is given the task of maintaining his wheelchair, which makes Sheldon envious. (S5 Ep21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Stag Convergence: Leonard, Sheldon and Raj throw a bachelor party for Howard, during which some stories about his sexual history are accidentally revealed. (S5 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Launch Acceleration: When NASA inform Howard that his space mission has been rescheduled to an earlier date, he tries to use the wedding as an excuse not to go. (S5 Ep23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Countdown Reflection: Bernadette decides that she wants to get married to Howard before his NASA space mission, but can they get organised in time? (S5 Ep24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Little Big Mom: When Marge breaks her leg in a skiing accident, Lisa takes over running the Simpson household, and Homer and Bart end up moving to a leper colony in Hawaii. (S11 Ep10/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: How I Spent My Strummer Vacation: Homer goes to a rock 'n' roll camp. When it's time to leave, he just wants to keep rockin' with Mick Jagger, Keith Richards and Lenny Kravitz. (S14 Ep2/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Great Celebrity Bake Off
E4Plus1.uk.description: for Stand Up To Cancer: Kelly Brook, Mo Gilligan, Carol Vorderman and Rob Rinder tackle signature sandwich biscuits, iced buns, and a cake showstopper revealing their guilty pleasure!

E4Plus1.uk.title: Big Fat Quiz: Best Bits
E4Plus1.uk.description: Things get spicy for host Jimmy Carr and a roster of comedy rivals, including Michael McIntyre, Davina McCall and Lee Mack, in an episode celebrating rivalry on the Big Fat Quiz. (Ep2/4)

E4Plus1.uk.title: New: Dating Naked UK
E4Plus1.uk.description: Brand new series - Winning Connections: It's the final, and the final three couples set about proving their connections - and disproving others' - to win the £50,000 prize. (S1 Ep10)

Film4.uk.title: The Unbearable Weight of...
Film4.uk.description: ...Massive Talent: (2022) Nicolas Cage stars as, er, Nic Cage - an unbearably talented actor caught up in a CIA investigation while trying to resurrect his ailing career. With Pedro Pascal.

Film4.uk.title: The Quiet Girl
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Colm Bairéad's poignant drama about a little girl who's sent away from home to live with distant family in rural Ireland. Based on Claire Keegan's novella Foster. In Gaelic/subs.

Film4.uk.title: Spencer
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Kristen Stewart dons the famous pixie cut to play an embattled Princess Diana in director Pablo Larraín's stylised dramatisation of three stifling Christmas nights at Sandringham.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Teleshopping
Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Payroll
Film4.uk.description: (1961) British crime thriller starring Billie Whitelaw. When Jackie's husband - an armoured van driver - is killed in a heist, she vows to unmask those responsible and take her revenge.

Film4.uk.title: A Lawless Street
Film4.uk.description: (1955) A non-stop romp of a western from director Joseph H Lewis. In the town of Medicine Bend, only Marshal Calem Ware can keep its citizens from falling into complete lawlessness.

Film4.uk.title: Oblivion Interview Special
Film4.uk.description: Tom Cruise talks about making the sci-fi-adventure Oblivion.

Film4.uk.title: The Colditz Story
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Classic Second World War drama. John Mills, Lionel Jeffries and Bryan Forbes star as just some of the POWs determined to break out of the infamous German 'escape-proof' prison.

Film4.uk.title: Jingle All the Way
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Brian Levant's festive all-action comedy. Arnold Schwarzenegger is on a mission to get his son (Jake Lloyd) the must-have Christmas toy, Turbo Man. But it's sold out everywhere...

Film4.uk.title: The Day After Tomorrow
Film4.uk.description: (2004) Tense sci-fi thriller starring Jake Gyllenhaal and Dennis Quaid. A scientist sets out to save his son when global warming plunges the world into a sudden climatic catastrophe.

Film4.uk.title: Wrath of Man
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Jason Statham reunites with director Guy Ritchie to give it both barrels as a mysterious hardman working for a money truck firm that keeps getting hit. But is he an inside man?

Film4.uk.title: The Mechanic
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Thriller with Jason Statham and Donald Sutherland. A hitman is ordered to kill his mentor, but then takes on the dead man's son as an apprentice. Could get complicated... and deadly.

Film4.uk.title: Carol
Film4.uk.description: (2015) Drama based on Patricia Highsmith's ground-breaking novel. A wealthy married woman (Cate Blanchett) falls in love with a younger woman (Rooney Mara) who works in a department store.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Cover Girl
Film4.uk.description: (1944) Rita Hayworth and Gene Kelly star in Charles Vidor's Technicolor comedy musical about a chorus girl's rise to fame. Featuring songs and a score from Jerome Kern and Ira Gershwin.

Film4.uk.title: Dead of Night
Film4.uk.description: (1945) Five uncanny tales of the supernatural in one eerie package, the most famous starring ventriloquist Michael Redgrave and a deadly dummy. Prepare to be spooked.

Film4.uk.title: Anastasia
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Historical drama. The Oscar-winning Ingrid Bergman stars as an amnesiac refugee who Yul Brynner tries to pass off as the daughter of the murdered Tsar of Russia, Nicholas II.

Film4.uk.title: Dr Who and the Daleks
Film4.uk.description: (1965) A spin-off of the cult television series starring Peter Cushing. Backyard-inventor Dr Who finds himself stuck on the irradiated planet Skaro, home of the cold and metallic Daleks.

Film4.uk.title: Rosaline
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Literary romcom with Kaitlyn Dever and Isabela Merced. This is the story of Juliet's cousin who gets dumped by Romeo at the start of Shakespeare's play... and she's not too pleased.

Film4.uk.title: Mrs Harris Goes to Paris
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Lesley Manville stars as a cleaner who saves up and heads to Paris to get herself a Dior couture dress, in director Anthony Fabian's fabulous, Oscar-nominated period comedy drama.

Film4.uk.title: American Gangster
Film4.uk.description: (2007) True crime thriller directed by Ridley Scott. An outcast New York cop (Russell Crowe) is charged with bringing down entrepreneurial Harlem drug lord Frank Lucas (Denzel Washington).

Film4.uk.title: Thief
Film4.uk.description: (1971) Crime thriller starring Richard Crenna. A recently paroled thief must do one last job to pay off old debts. But can he get away with it and build a life with his new girlfriend?

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: The Desert Fox
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Drama. James Mason stars in Henry Hathaway's sympathetic portrait of Field Marshal Erwin Rommel in the final years of his life during the Second World War. With Jessica Tandy.

Film4.uk.title: The Lavender Hill Mob

Film4.uk.description: (2022) Drama starring Emma Thompson as a recently widowed, retired teacher who has a sexual bucket list she wants to get around to now that she has the time and, perhaps, even the energy.

Film4.uk.description: (2018) Tom Cruise stars in part six of the action-thriller series. His mission: to stop terrorists from getting their hands on nuclear bombs and unleashing global devastation.

GBNews.uk.title: Patrick Christys Tonight
GBNews.uk.description: Join Patrick for two hours of spirited debate and news making interviews. Top guests tackle the issues that matter, with a sharp take on every story.

GBNews.uk.title: Patrick Christys Tonight Late Edition
GBNews.uk.description: Tomorrow's news, tonight. All the major stories making the front pages and full coverage of all the breaking news at home and abroad with Patrick Christys.

GBNews.uk.title: The Late Show Live
GBNews.uk.description: Live from Washington DC, Bev Turner and Ben Leo bring you the latest from the US and what it means for Britain.

GBNews.uk.title: Farage
GBNews.uk.description: Nigel Farage doesn't hold back in his GB News prime-time show. Hear his views and give your own in an hour of discussion and debate. Join Nigel as he takes on the big stories other media won't touch.

GBNews.uk.title: Patrick Christys Tonight
GBNews.uk.description: Join Patrick for two hours of spirited debate and news making interviews. Top guests tackle the issues that matter, with a sharp take on every story.

GBNews.uk.title: Patrick Christys Tonight Late...
GBNews.uk.description: Edition. Tomorrow's news, tonight. All the major stories making the front pages and full coverage of all the breaking news at home and abroad with Patrick Christys.

GBNews.uk.title: Breakfast with Eamonn and Ellie
GBNews.uk.description: Join Eamonn Holmes & Ellie Costello to start your day across the United Kingdom. This is your breakfast show. Join the conversation about what is happening in our nation and the world.

GBNews.uk.title: Britain's Newsroom
GBNews.uk.description: Andrew and Miriam present Monday to Thursday mornings. When the news happens, it happens here. GB News brings you the biggest stories and the answers you need from across the UK.

GBNews.uk.title: PMQs Live
